              }
            ],
            "text": "Activity"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " - Celebrating both boys' birthdays!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "strong"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Accomplishment"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " - Getting the second COVID vaccine and surviving having a horrible stomach virus at the same time as the whole rest of the family (I wouldn't wish that on anybody!)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "April was a month of celebrating our boys! Caden turned 1 on the 6th, and Carson turned 3 on the 24th! We also celebrated the life of Daniel's Grandma in St. Petersburg, FL, who went to be with Jesus on Easter morning."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Photos from the month, top left to bottom right:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/SFTM_April-2021_EverydayAccountsBlog.com_1.png",
              "alt": "SFTM_April 2021_EverydayAccountsBlog.com",
              "title": null
            },
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/SFTM_April-2021_EverydayAccountsBlog.com_1.png",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(1) Caden is doing really well at swim lessons. He's up to four seconds under water, and he loves his teacher Mr. Ryan!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(2) Daniel and his boys at the playground :)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(3) This was outside of Easter brunch. How cute are these brothers all dressed up for Easter?! We had a fun egg hunt at home and also opened Easter baskets after nap time."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(4) I took Caden for his one year appointment at the pediatrician. This was our first visit after the tragic loss of our own pediatrician Dr. Dodson. This sign was set up outside of their temporary location. We truly do miss and love Dr. Dodson."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/SFTM_April-2021_EverydayAccountsBlog.com_2.png",
              "alt": "SFTM_April 2021_EverydayAccountsBlog.com",
              "title": null
            },
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/SFTM_April-2021_EverydayAccountsBlog.com_2.png",
