          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/SFTM_April-2021_EverydayAccountsBlog.com_2.png",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "("
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "1) On Caden's actual birthday, Daniel took the day off, and we all went to Little Land Play Gym. The boys LOVED this place. They were especially drawn to this giant light-up pegboard."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(2) My baby is one! We've made it through a lot this year together, so there was much to celebrate."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(3) Soaking in all the little moments with my one-year-old!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(4) Unfortunately, later that week, we all got a horrible stomach bug. It started with Carson (who we actually took to the emergency room in the middle of the night), then Daniel, then me, then Caden. This is Caden sleeping in our bed so we could help him when he got sick. :( We had to postpone the family party we had planned for him to the first weekend of May."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/SFTM_April-2021_EverydayAccountsBlog.com_3.png",
              "alt": "SFTM_April 2021_EverydayAccountsBlog.com",
              "title": null
            },
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/SFTM_April-2021_EverydayAccountsBlog.com_3.png",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(1) Caden's first haircut! He's needed one for a long time. When he was about four months, he went bald on the sides and back of his head, but he kept a little \"mohawk\" in the top middle, which grew into long hair over his eyes by the time he was 10 months! He was very overdue for a trim. He had a lot of fun getting his hair cut. This is a \"before\" pic."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(2) And this is Caden after the haircut! All smiles!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(3) As I mentioned earlier, Daniel and I went to St. Pete, FL for his grandmother's memorial service. It was wonderful to get together with family and share all of the wonderful, funny stories about her."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(4) Caden can CLIMB almost anything he can reach now, including the bathroom stool. I definitely have my hands full!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/SFTM_April-2021_EverydayAccountsBlog.com_4.png",
              "alt": "SFTM_April 2021_EverydayAccountsBlog.com",
              "title": null
            },
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/SFTM_April-2021_EverydayAccountsBlog.com_4.png",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(1) For Carson's birthday weekend, we checked into the Kalahari Resort in Round Rock! We had so so much fun. We enjoyed the wave pool..."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(2) ...the water swings..."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(3) ..the outdoor pool areas..."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(4)... and especially the slides for kids! We had a little family party in our hotel room Saturday and celebrated as much as we could in the middle of all the playing and splashing!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Have a great May! I just love May and look forward to looking back on the memories we will make this month."
          }
        ]
